h, annihilate, extirpate"},{"type":"entry","text":"querulous","headword":"querulous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.抱怨的，爱发牢骚的(habitually complaining; fretful)"},{"type":"text","text":"['kweralas]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：que（看作question，质疑）+rul（看作rule，规则）+ous（的）→质疑规"},{"type":"text","text":"则→抱怨的"},{"type":"text","text":"Safire as a political commentator is patently querulous, he writes biased"},{"type":"text","text":"editorials about every action the government takes."},{"type":"entry","text":"attest","headword":"attest"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 证明， 证实(to declare to be true or genuine)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'test]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：at（表加强）+test（证明）→证明"},{"type":"text","text":"图attestto证实，证明"},{"type":"text","text":"certify, testify, witness"}]},{"number":47,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"pompous","headword":"pompous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 自大的(having or exhibiting self-importance)"},{"type":"text","text":"['pa:mpas]"},{"type":"text","text":"arrogant"},{"type":"entry","text":"enamored","headword":"enamored"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj倾心的，被迷住(inflamed with love; fascinated)"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：en（使）+amor(爱）+ed→珍爱的→倾心的"},{"type":"text","text":"[1'namard]"},{"type":"text","text":"be enamored of 珍爱..，喜爱."},{"type":"text","text":"bewitched, captivated, charmed, enchanted, infatuated"},{"type":"entry","text":"rigorous","headword":"rigorous"},{"type":"text","text":"adi严格的，严够的（manifesting, exercising. or favoring"},{"type":"text","text":"['rrgaras]"},{"type":"text","text":"rigor)"},{"type":"text","text":"diverse"},{"type":"text","text":"austere, rigid, severe, stern"},{"type":"entry","text":"diverse","headword":"diverse"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不同的(different, dissimilar)：多样的(diversified)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dar'vs:rs]"},{"type":"text","text":"词根记亿：d（离开）+vers（转）+e→转开→不同的"},{"type":"text","text":"disparate, distant, divergent"},{"type":"text","text":"diversity(n.多样，千变万化)：diversity[v（使）多样化]"},{"type":"entry","text":"rehabilitate","headword":"rehabilitate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v使恢复（健康、能力、地位等)to restore to a former health,capacity,rank,etc.)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ri:a'brltert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：re（重新）+habiit（看作abili，能）+ate→重新获得能力→使恢复"},{"type":"entry","text":"duplicate","headword":"duplicate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.复制的，两重的(consisting of or existing in two corresponding or identical"},{"type":"text","text":"['du:plikat]"},{"type":"text","text":"parts or examples)"},{"type":"entry","text":"officious","headword":"officious"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj过于殷勤的，多管闲事的(too ready or willing to give orders or advice;"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'fifas]"},{"type":"text","text":"meddlesome);非官方的(informal, unofficial)"},{"type":"entry","text":"grandeur","headword":"grandeur"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.壮丽，宏伟(splendor,magnificence)"},{"type":"text","text":"['graendzar]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自grand（adj.宏伟的，壮丽的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"amorphous","headword":"amorphous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无固定形状的(without definite form; shapeless)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'mo:rfas]"},{"type":"text","text":"国词根记忆：a（没有）+morph（形状）+ous→无固定形状的"},{"type":"entry","text":"withhold","headword":"withhold"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 抑制(to hold back from action);扣留，保留(to keep on purpose)"},{"type":"text","text":"[wid'hauld]"},{"type":"text","text":"国联想记忆：with（附带着）+hold（拿住）→保留"}]},{"number":48,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 03 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"articulate","headword":"articulate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.清楚地说话(to express clearly)：(用关节）连接（to put together by joints)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a:r'trkjulert]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆联想记忆：art（关节）+iculate→像关节一样（字字入扣）→清楚地说话"},{"type":"text","text":"enunciate"},{"type":"text","text":"articulately（adv.善于表达地：发音清晰地）：unarticulated（adj.表达不清的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"preclude","headword":"preclude"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 预防，排除(to rule out in advance; prevent)：限ib(to exclude or prevent (sb.)"},{"type":"text","text":"[prr'klu:d]"},{"type":"text","text":"from a given condition or activity)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：pre（预先）+clud（关闭）+e→预先关闭→预防，排除"},{"type":"text","text":"deter, forestall, forfend, obviate, ward"},{"type":"entry","text":"accessible","headword":"accessible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj易接近的（easy to approach)：易受影响的(open to the influence of)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ak'sesabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"accessible to达到"},{"type":"text","text":"employable, operative, practicable, unrestricted, usable"},{"type":"entry","text":"pristine","headword":"pristine"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj原始的(belonging to the earliest period or state)：质朴的，纯洁的(not"},{"type":"text","text":"['prrsti:n]"},{"type":"text","text":"spoiled or corrupted by civilization; pure) ; 新鲜的, 干净的(fresh and clean)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：pri（看作prim，第一，首先）+st（站）+ine→站在首位的→原始的"},{"type":"text","text":"Scientists’ pristine reputation as devotees of the disinterested pursuit of"},{"type":"text","text":"truth has been compromised by recent evidence that some scientists have"},{"type":"text","text":"deliberately fabricated experimental results to further their own careers."},{"type":"entry","text":"disproportionate","headword":"disproportionate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不成比例的(being out of proportion)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,drspra'po:rfanat]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：dis（不）+proportion(比例）+ate(-的）→不成比例的"},{"type":"entry","text":"commend","headword":"commend"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.推荐；举荐（to recommend as worthy of confidence or notice)：表扬；称赞（to"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka'mend]"},{"type":"text","text":"praise)"},{"type":"text","text":"acclaim, applaud, compliment, praise, recommend"},{"type":"text","text":"commendation（n.黄扬，称赞）"},{"type":"entry","text":"epitome","headword":"epitome"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.典型(sb./sth. showing all the typical qualities of sth.):梗概(abstract,"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'prtami]"},{"type":"text","text":"summary, abridgment)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：epi（在后面）+tom（切）+e→在（书）后面切割出的要点→梗概；单词"},{"type":"text","text":"tome意为“卷，册”"},{"type":"text","text":"epitomize （v.概括，摘要）"},{"type":"entry","text":"proficient","headword":"proficient"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 熟练的，精通的(skilful, expert)"},{"type":"text","text":"[pra'fi{nt]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：pro（在前）+fic（做）+ient→之前做过的→熟练的"},{"type":"text","text":"Experienced and proficient Susan is a good, reliable trumpeter; her music is"},{"type":"text","text":"often more satistying than Carol's brilliant but erratic playing."},{"type":"entry","text":"adept","headword":"adept"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.熟练的，擅长的(highly skilled，expert)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'dept]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ad（加强）+ept掌握）→有能力→熟练的，擅长的"},{"type":"text","text":"图be adept at 擅长"},{"type":"entry","text":"dissent","headword":"dissent"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 异议(difference of opinion) v. 不同意，持异议(to differ in belief or opinion;"},{"type":"text","text":"[di'sent]"},{"type":"text","text":"disagree)"}]},{"number":49,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"text","text":"Even though political editorializing was not forbidden under the new regime,"},{"type":"text","text":"journalists still experienced discreet, though perceptible, governmental pressure"},{"type":"text","text":"to limit dlissent."},{"type":"text","text":"dissension（n.意见分歧；不和）"},{"type":"entry","text":"overwrought","headword":"overwrought"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj紧张过度的，兴奋过度的（very nervousorexcited）"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvar'ro:t]"},{"type":"entry","text":"susceptible","headword":"susceptible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj易受影响的，敏感的(unresistant to some stimulus, influence, or agency)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'septabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"Because it has no distinct and recognizable typographical form and few"},{"type":"text","text":"recurring narrative conventions, the novel is, of all literary genres, the least"},{"type":"text","text":"susceptible to definition."},{"type":"entry","text":"aesthetic","headword":"aesthetic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 美学的，审美的(relating to aesthetics or the beautiful)"},{"type":"text","text":"[es'0etrk]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：aesthe（感觉）+tic（的）→对美有感觉的→审美的"},{"type":"entry","text":"clumsy","headword":"clumsy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.笨拙的(lacking grace;awkward)：拙劣的(ill-"},{"type":"text","text":"['klAmzi]"},{"type":"text","text":"constructed)"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：c+lum（亮度）+Sy→没有亮光，不灵光→"},{"type":"text","text":"笨拙的"},{"type":"text","text":"gawky. lumbering, lumpish"},{"type":"entry","text":"moralistic","headword":"moralistic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.道学的，说教的（concermed with morals)"},{"type":"text","text":"[mo:ra'lrstrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自moral（n.道德）"},{"type":"text","text":"clumsy"},{"type":"entry","text":"frustrate","headword":"frustrate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v挫败，使沮丧（to baffle,defeat)"},{"type":"text","text":"['frastrert]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：frust（一部分）+rate（费用）→买东西只带了一部分钱，买不成→挫败"},{"type":"text","text":"foil, thwart"},{"type":"entry","text":"surmount","headword":"surmount"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.克服，战胜(to prevail over; overcome);登上(to get to the top of)"}]},{"number":50,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"relinquish","headword":"relinquish"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 放弃,让出(to give up:; withdraw or retreat from)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'lrnkw]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：re（相反）+linqu（离开）+ish→离开→放弃，让出"},{"type":"entry","text":"redundant","headword":"redundant"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 累整的, 多余的(exceeding what is necessary or normal; superfluous)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'dandant]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：red（看作re，回）+und（波动）+ant→波动回来的→回流的→累赞的，"},{"type":"text","text":"多余的"},{"type":"text","text":"diffuse, prolix, verbose, wordy"},{"type":"entry","text":"zenith","headword":"zenith"},{"type":"d